diff:1667577082:1667577080:=1,90d0%0a%3c (:if [ authgroup @tas || authgroup @admins || equal {$Author} '' ]:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=edit|Edit this page]] \\%0a%3c Status: {GradebookArticles.{$Name}$:Status} %0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c [[!{$:Category}]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !Needs washed%0a%3c %0a%3c :Author: nkocurek%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Summary:''' \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Omitting the infinitive or gerund in favor of the past tense after needs%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c In some parts of the United States, it is common to say "needs washed" or "needs fixed" when something needs to be verb-ed. It makes the verb-ed form seem like an adjective, which is actually a concept I really like. We already do treat this form like an adjective in other contexts, like when you say "The shirt is washed", it makes it sound like washed is an adjective describing shirt.%0a%3c %0a%3c The "correct" form in Standard White American English would be "needs to be washed" or "needs washing". The first example adds the infinitive and the second example replaces with the gerund "-ing" expressing that it needs the action to be done, rather than the action needs to have been done.%0a%3c %0a%3c My speculation is that this is something as a reduction from the infinitive, much like how contractions have become commonplace, albeit on a larger scale, cutting out "to be".%0a%3c %0a%3c Yale Grammatical Diversity Project notes that this diversity is found particularly in the US Midwest, from Pennsylvania to Kansas. From the site's map data, it is not particularly common in any big cities outside of Pittsburgh.%0a%3c %0a%3c I particularly chose this one because it is something I have heard from my relatives who live in rural Central Pennsylvania.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:Section: C:)%0a%3c (:Category: MorphosyntacticDiversityOfEnglish:)%0a%3c (:Title: Needs washed:)%0a
